The paper discusses bibliometric performance and citation-based relevance attribution, which are commonly studied in the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and scientometrics (cs.ST). The focus on the impact of Chinese publications suggests a potential connection to the subfield of computational social science (cs.CY), which often examines the impact of social and cultural factors on scientific output. Finally, the mention of Asian countries benefiting more from Chinese publications could also relate to the subfield of social informatics (cs.SI), which studies the intersection of technology and society.
